\subsection{Level of a Hilbert modular form}
\begin{definition}\label{mf.hilbert.level_norm}
\uses{nf,nf.ideal.label.hmf,nf.ring_of_integers,nf.totally_real}
Given a Hilbert modular form $f$ that is defined in terms of the {{ KNOWL('nf.totally_real', "totally real") }} {{ KNOWL('nf', "number field") }} $F$, the **level** of $f$ is a nonzero ideal $\mathfrak{N}$ of the {{ KNOWL('nf.ring_of_integers', "ring of integers") }} $\Z_F$ of $F$ that determines the group $\Gamma_0(\mathfrak{N})$ under which $f$ transforms. In the LMFDB, such an ideal $\mathfrak{N}$ is identified by a {{ KNOWL("nf.ideal.label.hmf", "label")}}.

The **level norm** is the absolute norm of the level of the form.
\end{definition}


